    <descript>
      <abstract>This feature class contains wastewater structures & corresponding information that falls within the boundary of Loudoun County.</abstract>
      <purpose>To provide spatially correct location & information for sanitary sewer within Loudoun County.</purpose>
      <supplinf>Data are stored in the corporate ArcSDE Geodatabase as a point feature class. The coordinate system is Virginia State Plane (North), Zone 4501, datum NAD83 HARN (vertical datum, if applicable, NAVD88), US Survey foot units.

LCSA (Loudoun County Sanitary Authority) provides two Datasets to Loudoun County Office of Mapping & Geographic Information (OMAGI): Waste water and Water to OMAGI.  These two datasets are combined and four new datasets created from the source data: Wastewater_Line, Wastewater_Point, Water_Line, &amp; Water_Point.</supplinf>
    </descript>

      <procstep>
        <procdesc>Wastewater structures feature class derived from source Wastewater dataset & feature classes: wwJunctionChamber, wwManhole, wwPumpStation, wwTreatmentPlant, & wwVault.

- Create a new field in allsource datasets called LCSAType to identify structure type.
- Populate new field in all datasets with appropriate structure type: Junction Chamber, Manhole, Pump Station, Treatment Plant, & Vault.
- Union all five source datasets to produce LCSA_WASTEWATER_POINT
-- Drop all attribute fields except for LifecycleStatus, Owner, LocationDescrip, wwType, Comment, InvertA, InvertB, InvertC, InvertOut, InFromA, InFromB, InFromC, LCSAType, ChamberName, StationName, PlantName, & VaultName</procdesc>
